            "heading": "<p>Overpronation</p>",
            "heading_size": "title-md",
            "heading_tag": "h2",
            "highlighted_text": "text",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "text_LHGLnM": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Overpronation, or flat feet, is a common biomechanical issue where the arch collapses upon weight bearing, causing stress or inflammation on the plantar fascia. This condition can lead to discomfort and contribute to other foot problems. This added stress can result in conditions such as Plantar Fasciitis,<br/> Heel Spurs, Metatarsalgia, Post-tib Tendonitis, and Bunions.<br/><br/>Causes of flat feet include obesity, pregnancy, or repetitive pounding on hard surfaces, which weaken the arch.</p>",
            "text_font": "body",
            "text_size": "subtext-md",
            "text_max_size": 32,
            "text_line_height": 1.6,
            "text_letter_spacing": 0,
